IUserControlTypeResolutionService Interface

Definition

Defines the method a class must implement to return a control's type for a specified tag prefix and tag name.

In this Article

public interface IUserControlTypeResolutionService

Remarks

Page developers and control authors do not use the IUserControlTypeResolutionService interface. The IUserControlTypeResolutionService interface is implemented by tool developers to return the Type of a control identified by a tag prefix and tag name.

Methods

GetType(String,String)

Retrieves a type based on a parsed ASP.NET tag prefix and the name of the tag.

public Type GetType (string tagPrefix, string tagName);
tagPrefix
String

The parsed prefix of an ASP.NET tag.

tagName
String

The name of the parsed ASP.NET tag.

Returns
Type

A Type that represents the type of control the prefix and tag identify.

Remarks

Designer environments implement this method to provide a way for ASP.NET parsers and designers to resolve user control types at design time.
